## Analytics filters (client-only)

- State: `app.analyticsPersonFilter` (empty = all), `app.analyticsLocationFilter` (empty = all). Not cleared on month change.
- UI: `#analyticsPersonFilter`, `#analyticsLocationFilter`, `#analyticsFilterHint` above the stat grids.
- Scope: task + points stats, contribution bars, daily heatmap, month-over-month (current vs previous month both use the same filters). **Does not** change the activity log (`#logList`); use log search there.
- Location: an entry matches only if `locationIds` includes the selected location (entries with no locations excluded when a location is selected).

## Log search / filter (client-only)

- State: `app.logSearchQuery` (string). Cleared when the month dropdown changes (`switchMonth`).
- UI: `#logSearch` under “Log for …”; styles in `chore-tracker-forms.css`.
- Matching: `entryMatchesLogSearch` — whitespace tokens AND; haystack = date, chore, person, locations, points. Only affects `#logList`.

## Scheduled log suggestions (client-only)

- Shown when a scheduled chore is **overdue**, **due today**, or **due within 3 days** (`scheduledStatus` `soon`), and its **title matches a chore preset** (exact case-insensitive, or close fuzzy match via `presetMatchingScheduledTitle` — e.g. “Wipe …” vs “Wiped …”).
- Renders under “Log a chore”, above Quick log. Tap fills `#inChore` (and per-location selects like quick log); user picks person/date and **Add**. Does **not** call scheduled “complete” API — use Scheduled dashboard **Mark done** to reset the timer.

---

## Feature map

### Auth and server

- **Households (multi-tenant)** — isolated stores under **`data/households/<id>/`**; **scrypt** password hashes per household slug (`[a-z0-9][a-z0-9_-]{0,62}`) live in SQLite **`data/households/registry.db`** (Node **22+**). Legacy **`registry.json`** is imported once then renamed to **`registry.json.migrated`**. On first start, legacy **`data/chores.json`** is moved to **`data/households/default/chores.json`** and the registry seeds household **`default`** with password from **`CHORELOG_PASSWORD`** (default `monkey`). **`POST /api/households`** (no auth cookie) creates a household when **`CHORELOG_OPEN_REGISTRATION=1`** (body **`id`**, **`password`** ≥8 chars) **or** when **`CHORELOG_MASTER_PASSWORD`** is set and **`masterPassword`** in the body matches; otherwise **`403`** JSON. **`409`** if the id already exists.
- **Login** — `POST /api/login` with **`household`**, **`username`** (display name for audit), **`password`**; **logout** `POST /api/logout`. Session cookie payload **`v:2`** includes **`household`** + **`user`**.
- **Login members (unauthenticated)** — **`POST /api/login/members`** with **`household`**, **`password`** — same password check as login; returns **`{ people: string[] }`** from the household store’s **People** list (sorted). Same brute-force throttle as login on failures; used by the login UI **step 1 → step 2** (pick a person from a dropdown). Does not set a session.
- **Registration (unauthenticated)** — **`GET /api/register-info`** — `{ openRegistration, hasMasterPassword, allowCreateHousehold }` for the login **Create account** tab (create vs join household, master field visibility). Login UI: **Sign in** vs **Create account**; join = household + password then member dropdown; create = **`POST /api/households`** then member dropdown then **`POST /api/login`**.
- **Account (authenticated)** — **`GET /api/account`** — `{ user, household, sessionExpiresAt, canCreateHouseholds (master password set), openRegistration }`. **`PUT /api/account/display-name`** — JSON **`{ user }`**; re-issues cookie with updated display name. **`POST /api/account/password`** — JSON **`{ currentPassword, newPassword }`** (≥8); updates **this household’s** registry password after verifying the current password.
- **Brute-force protection** — failed sign-ins are tracked **per client IP** (`lib/login-throttle.cjs`); after `CHORELOG_LOGIN_MAX_FAILURES` (default 8) failures within `CHORELOG_LOGIN_WINDOW_MS` (default 15 min), the IP is locked out for `CHORELOG_LOGIN_LOCKOUT_MS` (default 15 min). State in **`data/login-throttle.json`** (survives restarts). **`429`** with `Retry-After` and JSON `{ error, retryAfterSeconds }` when locked out. **`CHORELOG_TRUST_PROXY=1`** sets Express `trust proxy` so `req.ip` reflects `X-Forwarded-For` behind a reverse proxy.
- **Session** — signed HMAC cookie (`chorelog_auth`) includes **`user`** and **`household`**; ~30-day expiry; secret from `CHORELOG_SECRET` (dev default in code). **`GET /api/auth`** returns `{ authenticated, user, household }` when valid.
- **API guard** — unauthenticated: **`GET /api/auth`**, **`GET /api/version`**, **`GET /api/register-info`**, **`GET /api/openapi.json`**, **`POST /api/login`**, **`POST /api/login/members`**, **`POST /api/logout`**, **`POST /api/households`**. Everything else under **`/api/*`** requires a valid cookie tied to a known household (`requireApiAuth` sets `req.authPayload`, `req.householdId`).
- **OpenAPI (integrators)** — **`GET /api/openapi.json`** returns OpenAPI **3.0.3** JSON; `servers[0].url` reflects the request host. Source: **`lib/openapi-spec.cjs`** (`buildOpenApiDocument`). Committed snapshot: **`docs/openapi.json`** (regenerate with **`npm run docs:openapi`** after spec edits). **`scripts/check-api-routes.cjs`** ensures every `app.(get|post|put|delete)('/api/…')` in **`server.js`** matches a path+method in the spec (also runs at end of **`npm test`**; CI fails on drift).
- **When changing HTTP routes** — (1) implement in **`server.js`** (and **`requireApiAuth`** bypass list if public). (2) Update **`lib/openapi-spec.cjs`** (`paths`, `components`, `tags` as needed). (3) Run **`npm run docs:openapi`** to refresh **`docs/openapi.json`**. (4) Run **`npm test`** (includes route check). (5) Adjust **`.rctx`** Feature map / API guard bullets if behavior or auth changed.
- **Persistence (per household)** — JSON **`data/households/<id>/chores.json`** (atomic write). **Optional SQLite**: if **`CHORELOG_SQLITE_PATH`** is set (any non-empty value), each household uses **`data/households/<id>/chores.db`** (`node:sqlite`, WAL); empty DB imports sibling **`chores.json`** once. **`ensureSeed`** seeds demo data per household when empty.
- **Version** — **`GET /api/version`** — without auth: `version`, `nodeVersion`, `exportSchemaVersion`, `multiHousehold`. With cookie: also **`household`**, **`persistence`**, **`databaseRelativePath`**, optional SQLite engine fields. Footer + Settings **About** tab.

### Data model (store)

- **Entries** — `d`, `c`, `p`, optional `choreId`, `locationIds`, `createdAt` / `updatedAt`.
- **People & locations** — editable lists; at least one each enforced in UI.
- **Chore presets** — `title`, `points` (clamped), hex `color`, `scoringMode` `flat` | **`per_location`**.
- **Quick bar** — up to **24** preset ids validated against presets.
- **Scheduled chores** — `intervalDays`, `startsOn`, `lastCompletedAt`, **`reminderEnabled`** (omit or true = include in overdue webhook reminders), timestamps; next due from last completion or start date.
- **`discordWebhook`** — `enabled`, `url` (Discord), `reminderIntervalMinutes`, **`quietHoursEnabled`**, **`quietHoursStart`/`End`** (server local `HH:MM`), **`slackWebhookUrl`** (`hooks.slack.com`), **`genericWebhookUrl`** (HTTPS, Discord-shaped JSON); see `normalizeDiscordWebhook` in `server.js`.
- **Audit log** — `auditLog[]` (`id`, `at`, `actor`, `action`, `target`, optional `detail`); newest first; capped (e.g. 500); one household store = one audit stream.

### Chore logging

- **Main form** — date, person, chore text, multi-select locations (for `per_location` presets).
- **Semicolon bundles** — `;` separates multiple preset/title segments in one submit; server/client resolve rows (`resolveChorePayloadRows`).
- **Preset resolution** — optional `choreId` + free-text `c`; points from preset + locations when applicable.
- **Quick log** — one tap from bar; **`fillChoreFromPreset`** sets chore field + locations when none selected for per-location presets.
- **Custom suggestions** — `chore-input-suggest.js`: preset picker **per segment** (query after last `;`), keyboard/mouse, color stripe from preset; avoids whole-field `<datalist>` matching.
- **Add toast** — success message + **Undo** (removes last created entries via API).

### Activity log (month-scoped)

- **List** — current **month** only (from month selector); sorted by date descending.
- **Row UI** — date, chore text, person chip; **preset color** left border when `choreId` set; **+N pts** and **location names** when present.
- **Edit** — dialog with date, chore (datalist), person, locations; **`PUT /api/entries/:id`**.
- **Delete** — confirm dialog; **`DELETE /api/entries/:id`**.
- **Log search** — client-only AND-of-tokens across date/chore/person/locations/points; cleared on month change.

### Analytics and dashboard

- **Month picker** — options from distinct entry months (newest first); drives all dashboard + log views.
- **Dual metrics** — **task counts** vs **preset points** (parallel stat cards, bars, MoM columns).
- **Stat cards** — totals, most active / top earner, active days, members with activity, **balance %** (fairness across people), avg points per task (points grid).
- **Contribution bars** — per-person horizontal bars for tasks and points (separate max scaling).
- **Heatmap** — tasks per calendar day in selected month; intensity vs busiest day; weekday header; “busiest day” footer; respects analytics filters.
- **Analytics filters** — **person** and **location** (entry must include location when filtered); apply to stats, bars, heatmap, MoM — **not** the activity log.
- **Month-over-month** — previous month vs current for tasks and points; **% change** with up/down styling; handles “no previous month”.

### Scheduled chores

- **Intervals** — day, week, 2–3 weeks, ~month, 2–3 months (stored as `intervalDays`).
- **Due logic** — overdue / today / soon (≤3 days) / later (`scheduled-logic.js`); human-readable next due.
- **Main dashboard strip** — cards with status + **Mark done**; section **hidden** when there are no scheduled chores.
- **Manage dialog** — add (title + interval), list with **start date** edits, **per-chore “Remind when overdue (webhooks)”** checkbox (`reminderEnabled`), remove; **`PUT`/`DELETE`** routes.
- **Mark done flow** — dialog picks person; **`POST .../complete`** adds log line with scheduled title and resets timer; optional **`completedDate`** (calendar day).
- **Overdue reminders** — optional **Discord**, **Slack** (`hooks.slack.com`), **generic HTTPS** URLs, and/or **Web Push** to subscribed PWA devices (VAPID); **quiet hours** (server local clock, can span midnight); per-chore **`reminderEnabled`**; **server timer** + min interval per chore (`discordReminderSentAt`); **test** and **post overdue now** endpoints.
- **Log-form suggestions** — buttons for urgent scheduled titles that **match a preset** (exact/fuzzy); fill chore + locations only; does not complete scheduled item (use Mark done for timer).

### Settings and data lifecycle

- **Settings layout** — tabbed **nav** (`#settingsNav`, categories: Interface, Household, Chores, Integrations, Account, Audit, Data, **About**); **About** loads **`GET /api/version`** (app version, Node, storage type, data file path, SQLite engine + journal mode when applicable, export schema version); scrollable **panel** content; hamburger + backdrop on small viewports; last tab in `sessionStorage` (`chorelog-settings-tab`).
- **Account** — **`GET /api/account`** on open; session summary (household id, display name, expiry), edit display name (**`PUT /api/account/display-name`**), change household password (**`POST /api/account/password`**), optional **create household** (**`POST /api/households`**) when **`CHORELOG_OPEN_REGISTRATION=1`** and/or **`CHORELOG_MASTER_PASSWORD`** is set; **Log out** (**`POST /api/logout`**). `js/main.js`: `loadAccountPanel` / `loadAccountInfo`.
- **Integrations** — overdue reminders: Discord URL, reminder interval, **quiet hours**, optional **Slack** + **generic HTTPS** URLs; **browser push** on each device (Settings); Save / Send test / Post overdue now (`js/main.js`, `js/push-notifications.js`, `server.js`, `lib/push-send.cjs`).
- **Appearance** — theme **system / light / dark** (`localStorage` + inline head script to prevent flash); **`syncThemeMeta`** for `theme-color`.
- **People / locations / presets / quick bar** — CRUD in UI; **`PUT /api/settings`** batches updates.
- **Export** — **`GET /api/export`** (full JSON backup) and **`GET /api/export/entries.csv`** (log rows only, UTF-8 BOM, RFC 4180-style quoting); Settings → Data **Export JSON** / **Export CSV**.
- **Import** — file upload; **replace** or **merge** with confirmation; backup may include **`auditLog`** (export v5).
- **Audit log UI** — Settings → load **`GET /api/audit`** on open + Refresh; shows actor (signed-in account) and action summaries.
- **PWA** — `site.webmanifest` (standalone, icons); **`sw.js`** — installability hook, **no caching** of `/api` (see file comment); Apple touch icon / meta tags.

### Client infrastructure

- **`api-fetch.js`** — shared fetch behavior (e.g. auth failures).
- **Render registry** — breaks import cycles between render and main.
- **Responsive shell** — `--layout-max-width` steps at ~820px / 1100px / 1440px; log + MoM side-by-side on wide layouts.
- **i18n** — `localStorage` key `chorelog-locale` (`en` | `de`); nested JSON flattened to dotted keys; `t(key, vars)`; `initI18n()` in `chore-tracker.js` before `main.js`; Settings → Language; month names and dates use `getLocaleBcp47()` (`en-US` / `de-DE`).
- **Automated tests** — `npm test` runs **`node --test`** on `test/*.test.cjs`, then **`scripts/check-api-routes.cjs`** (OpenAPI vs `server.js`). Tests: `normalizeStore` (via `module.exports` from `server.js`, no listen/timer when required), **next due** for scheduled chores (**`lib/scheduled-recurrence.cjs`**, mirrored in **`js/utils/date.js`**), **semicolon resolve** rules (mirrors `resolveChorePayloadRows`), **household registry** JSON→SQLite migration (`test/households-registry.test.cjs`). GitHub Actions: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` on push/PR to `main`/`master`. Further ideas: HTTP import-merge, `scheduledStatus` labels with i18n stubs.

## Completed future ideas

- **Brute-force protection** — lockout on failed `POST /api/login` (`lib/login-throttle.cjs`, `data/login-throttle.json`). Details: **Auth and server**.
- **Optional SQLite backend** — `CHORELOG_SQLITE_PATH`, `lib/sqlite-store.cjs`, migration from JSON. Details: **Auth and server** (Persistence).
- **CSV / spreadsheet export** — `GET /api/export/entries.csv`, Settings → Data **Export CSV**.
- **Multi-household accounts** — isolated stores (`data/households/`), registry + login **`household`** field; **`POST /api/households`** with open registration and/or **`CHORELOG_MASTER_PASSWORD`**. Details: **Auth and server**.
- **OpenAPI for integrators** — **`GET /api/openapi.json`**, **`lib/openapi-spec.cjs`**, **`docs/openapi.json`**, route drift check. Details: **Auth and server** (OpenAPI bullet) and **When changing HTTP routes**.
- **Calendar-native recurrence** — scheduled chores support **`recurrence`**: `interval` (rolling **`intervalDays`**) or **`monthlyWeekday`** with **`monthOrdinal`** 1–4 (first–fourth weekday in month) or **5** (last such weekday), **`weekday`** 0–6 (Sun–Sat). Shared logic: **`lib/scheduled-recurrence.cjs`** / **`js/scheduled-recurrence.js`**; UI in scheduled dialog (**Repeat** + week/day). Server normalizes monthly rows with **`intervalDays`** 30 for legacy fields.
- **Web Push (PWA)** — alternative to Discord for overdue reminders: **`web-push`** + VAPID env keys; **`pushSubscriptions`** in household store; **`sw.js`** shows notifications; Integrations UI enables per device.

## Future ideas (implementation-oriented)

- **Soft delete** or archive for presets and log rows.
- **Fuzzy / typo-tolerant** matching for each `;` segment in the chore field (beyond current suggest list).
- **Backup snapshots** — timestamped copy of `chores.json` before destructive import or on a schedule.
- **True offline mode** — cache static assets + read-only queue in SW; conflict rules for writes.
- **Read-only or guest** role (view stats, no edit).
- **Tags or categories** orthogonal to presets.
- **Streaks / goals** — weekly targets, gentle nudges in UI.
- **Attachments** — optional photo per log entry (storage + privacy policy).
- **More locales** — extend `locales/*.json` and `SUPPORTED_LOCALES` in `js/i18n.js`.
- **Helm chart** or raw Kubernetes manifests for multi-replica deploys.

